{"word":"αὐτόφωρος","slug":"αὐτόφωρος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>αὐτόφωρος, ον</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:αὐτός\">αὐτός</a>, φώρ</el> ‘thief’] <b><i>self-incriminating,</i></b> the original association of this <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ adj.\">adj.</a> with self-incrimination in theft is <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ freq.\">freq.</a> extended in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Gk.\">Gk.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ lit.\">lit.</a> to any kind of crime, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ esp.\">esp.</a> in the phrase <el>ἐπ</el>’ <el>αὐτοφώρῳ</el> (caught) <i>in the act</i> (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> our ‘caught red-handed’) <b><a href='B:500 8:4'>J 8:4</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:αὐτοῦ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:αὐτόχειρ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}